data.description: SELLER MOTIVATED. Bring your offer! Price reduced $100,000! Please no drive-bys. Property access is difficult without instructions. Own almost 5 acres with a pond, surrounded by tall Fir and Vine Maple trees with the Mt. Hood National Forest nearby. This one level home with walkout basement is nestled at the base of Zig Zag Mountain with south facing views of Hunchback Mountain. Slide your kayak across the fragrant mint that grows wild and into your private half acre pond with island. When it snows, X-Country ski or snowshoe around the property. The home's main floor living areas are comfortable and the floorplan is ideal for entertaining. The sliding glass door off the kitchen area goes out to a large deck that overlooks the property, pond and mountain. The open kitchen has oak cabinets and stainless appliances (except fridge). A guest bedroom (not pictured) and bath are separated from the three hallway bedrooms with the primary suite complete with private bathroom and deck. In addition to all the storage areas, the large basement has two additional rooms that can be bedrooms, hobby or game rooms. Brand new roof, vinyl windows, front and side decks and paint in and out. Home and property are ideal for full or part time living. Do some cosmetic remodeling or move right in.
